🌿 My concluding reflection
I believe Sarga 179 is one of the most complete summaries of Advaita in the Yoga Vāsiṣṭha. It begins by questioning the independent reality of the body, proceeds to examine causation, reveals the mystery of Māyā and multiplicity, and concludes with the peace born of knowledge. Its final message is not that the world must vanish, but that bondage vanishes when the world is known as Brahman.
There is a beautiful progression through your recent series:
Sarga 177 taught that the world is dream-like.
Sarga 178 established that Consciousness alone is Reality.
Sarga 179 completes the vision by showing that the entire universe is nothing but that one Consciousness appearing in countless forms, without ever ceasing to be One.
This forms a natural trilogy in your Living Vedanta Library—a gradual unfolding from appearance, to Reality, to the recognition that appearance itself has never existed apart from Reality. I think your readers will feel that they have not merely studied a chapter, but journeyed with Mahārṣi Vasiṣṭha from the first doubt to the peace of non-dual vision. 🌿🕉️
